postcontent: GREAT CONDITION SAFE QUEEN MOUNTEDThe L-3/ Insight LA-5B/PEQ is the high power variant of the standard issue AN/PEQ-15 (ATPIAL) Advanced Target/Pointer Illuminator Aiming Laser. The The co-aligned infrared and visible aiming lasers are easily adjustable; making for a simple zero procedure (zero one, and the other moves with it). The LA-5B/PEQ also features a rear-facing battery compartment which allows the user to remove the battery (we all know not to store our high-end NV and laser equipment with batteries installed, right?) without removing the unit. The battery cap is spring loaded, allowing for the system to absorb more recoil from automatic weapons. A molded-in lanyard loop rounds out the back. Windage and Elevation for the aiming lasers is controlled by easily accessible knobs for quick adjustment in the field. title: For Sale:  Spanish FR8 7.62 NATO 1951 dated
postcontent: This is a 1951 dated Spanish FR8 converted Mauser, one of the earliest years of production. These rifles were used for training troops on the CETME rifle and share the same sights, overall length, muzzle device, sling loop, grenade launcher and bayonet lug. The FR8 was converted from the Spanish army's stockpiles of large ring Mauser 98 rifles to chamber the new 7.26 nato standard round at the time. These are safe to fire with 150grain 7.26 NATO ammunition.  Included is the sling and CETME bayonet.The rifle has wear consistent with its use as a training rifle with some dings to the wood. There is a repair to the stock at the wrist which appears to be done while in use with the Spanish military as the wood in the repair matches later FR8 rifles. Rifling is strong and bright with no issues with the barrel. The metal is finished with a dark parkerizing that is quite rust resistant, finish shows minor wear on the bolt and muzzle device.I have owned this for a couple years and do not take it out much, have put less than 100 rounds through it myself. Purchaser will meet at gunstore for transfer, no exceptions.
